entries.title: Crypto Magnates Cameron Winklevoss and Barry Silbert Trade Barbs
entries.description: Mr. Silbert’s Genesis is a lending partner of the earn program at Mr. Winklevoss’s Gemini.

entries.title: Southwest Meltdown Shows Airlines Need Tighter Software Integration
entries.description: The airline industry is long overdue for a tech overhaul that takes full advantage of the cloud and data integration, analysts say.

entries.title: Tesla Comes Up Short of 2022 Delivery Target as Growth Slows
entries.description: Elon Musk’s electric car maker fell short of its initial goal of increasing annual deliveries by 50% or more last year

entries.title: So You Worked for FTX. Now What? Advice From Recruiters and Employers
entries.description: Former employees of FTX will likely face extra scrutiny in their job hunt. But recruiters and hiring managers say they can move on if they are transparent and address the elephant in the room.

entries.title: TikTok Ban Debate Moves From Washington to Main Street
entries.description: A city council in South Dakota weighs measure to ban the ByteDance-owned app from municipal devices, pitting councilors against each other.

entries.title: Twitter Sued Over Rent Payment in San Francisco
entries.description: One of Twitter’s landlords accuses the social-media company of failing to pay for space in the building.
